editmore_vertUserThe following information is about my current project that this new package will be a part of, so let's make a few adjustments. Firstly we are using bun, not npm. My project uses NestJS with Express as the underlying HTTP platform.

Here's what I found:

Evidence of Express usage:

Dependencies in package.json: The project includes Express-related dependencies:

@nestjs/platform-express - NestJS's Express platform adapter
@types/express - TypeScript types for Express
@types/express-serve-static-core - Additional Express types
@types/express-session - Express session types
NestJS Application Structure: The main application files (src/main.ts and src/app.module.ts) follow the standard NestJS pattern:

NestFactory.create() in main.ts uses Express by default as the underlying HTTP server
The modular architecture is typical of NestJS applications
Key Point: While the project doesn't use Express directly, it leverages NestJS which runs on top of Express by default. NestJS provides a higher-level, more structured framework built on Express, giving you the benefits of Express's performance and ecosystem while providing better organization and features like dependency injection, decorators, and modular architecture.

The project appears to be a sophisticated backend service using NestJS with Express under the hood, along with additional technologies like TypeORM for database operations, Redis for caching, and various monitoring and MCP (Model Context Protocol) integrations.
